---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { QuizPlayer } from '../../components/quiz/QuizPlayer';
import quizData from '../../content/quizzes/autism-or-adhd.json';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Autism, ADHD, or Both? — Free Differential Quiz"
  description="Not sure if it's autism, ADHD, or AuDHD? This free 20-question quiz helps you explore where your traits lean. Takes 4-6 minutes."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Quizzes', href: '/quiz/' }, { label: 'Autism or ADHD?', href: '/quiz/autism-or-adhd/' }]}
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5 py-12">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-text">
        Autism, ADHD, or Both?
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-[0.9375rem] text-text-light leading-relaxed max-w-lg">
        Explore which traits feel most like your experience and whether AuDHD might be the best fit. 20 questions, takes about 6 minutes. Your answers stay private.
      </p>
    </header>

    <QuizPlayer quiz={quizData} client:load />

    <section class="mt-16 space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mb-4">How Is This Quiz Different?</h2>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          Unlike our flagship AuDHD quiz, this one focuses on <strong class="text-text">differentiating</strong>
          between autism and ADHD. Many traits look similar on the surface — social difficulties,
          sensory issues, executive function challenges — but the underlying reasons can be
          quite different. This quiz presents scenarios where autism-typical and ADHD-typical
          responses diverge, helping you see which pattern fits you better.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mb-4">Why Does It Matter Which One?</h2>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed">
          Understanding whether your traits are more autism-related, ADHD-related, or both
          can help with self-understanding, seeking the right kind of support, and finding
          strategies that actually work for your brain. What helps ADHD (like novelty and
          stimulation) can sometimes clash with what helps autism (like predictability and routine)
          — and knowing you have both can explain why some advice never quite fits.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
